        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Here's your cold outreach sequence. Three emails — pattern interrupt, proof, direct ask.\n\n---\n\n**Email 1 — The Insight**\n\nSubject: your Monday meeting\n\nMarcus here. I work with CEOs who built $10M-50M companies and then got stuck inside them.\n\nHere's what I see in every one of those companies: the CEO is making decisions that should belong to their directors. Not some of them — typically 40% or more. And the team isn't underperforming. They're waiting for permission.\n\nYou didn't hire adults to treat them like interns.\n\nI have a 14-day diagnostic called the Decision Audit. I sit in your meetings, talk to your team, and map exactly where your judgment is being used on problems that shouldn't reach you. No surveys. No personality tests.\n\nIf what I find doesn't surprise you, you owe me nothing.\n\n— Marcus\n\n---\n\n**Email 2 — The Proof**\n\nSubject: 47 decisions\n\nA CEO came to me running a $22M company. Smart guy. 65-hour weeks. Leadership team of four who wouldn't make a move without his approval.\n\nHe'd read the books. Hired a big-firm consultant — $80K for a strategy deck with nice charts. Nothing changed. Tried to \"just delegate more.\" Lasted two weeks.\n\nIn week one I sat in his meetings and didn't say a word. In week two I showed him that he'd personally made 47 decisions the prior week that should have belonged to his directors.\n\nHe had no idea.\n\n90 days later his Monday meetings went from 2 hours of status updates to 45 minutes of strategic decisions. He took a two-week vacation. Nothing broke.\n\nDecision debt compounds faster than financial debt. If you're curious what yours looks like, I'll show you in 14 days.\n\n— Marcus\n\n---\n\n**Email 3 — The Ask**\n\nSubject: one question\n\nIf you stepped away from your business for two weeks tomorrow, would it run without you?\n\nIf the honest answer is no — or \"probably, but I'd be checking my phone the whole time\" — that's a structural problem, not a people problem.\n\nI fix that. 90 days. If you don't see a measurable shift in your decision load, I refund the full engagement.\n\n15 minutes on the phone and I'll tell you whether I can help. If I can't, I'll tell you that too.\n\n— Marcus\n\n---\n\nWant me to save this to `03-Outputs/`? And we still have that soul extraction open whenever you want to come back to it."
